        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 10 at 3:35PM MDT until July 10 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 335 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles southeast
of Thurman, or 12 miles north of Flagler, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Mesonet. A 58 mph wind gust was reported north of Flagler.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Stratton, Flagler, Seibert, and Vona.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 403 and
424.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

This thunderstorm will produce strong winds resulting in areas of
near zero visibility in blowing dirt. Use extreme caution if you must
travel and be alert for rapidly changing visibility.</instruction>
